{
  "texts": [
    "Consequently, it becomes difficult to use aggregated national data and apply the previously mentioned approaches.",
    "In this case, the estimation and projection of national cancer incidence are generally performed in two steps (see for example Galceran et al., 2017).",
    "First, national incidence estimates for each year in the data series are derived using the Incidence/Mortality ratio (Sung et al., 2021).",
    "Then, projections are obtained using the above mentioned techniques.",
    "Retegui et al. (2023) propose an alternative approach to estimate cancer incidence in areas without registries."
  ]
}